## MAKE MYTH — STREAM STRUCTURE

**Current Chapter:** Athens Pilot Season (Mar → May 15, 2026)
**Schedule:** Tuesday + Thursday | 7:49 AM EST / 2:49 PM Athens (EET)
**Consistency is non-negotiable.** Same time every week unless exceptional circumstances occur.

### Stream Flow

```
Warmup (15–30 min pre-live)
  → Holdt Loop visual + proprietary music
  → Countdown timer
  → Rolling patron/member credits

↓ LIVE START (7:49 AM EST)

Intro (3–5 min)
  → Orient new viewers, explain episode focus

Writing Segment (45–90 min)
  → Notion | ONCE worldbuilding, scenes, lore
  → This is the core. The main event.

Gaming Segment (60–120 min)
  → Community decompression + interaction
  → Story-driven games, craft discussion

Closing (3–5 min)
  → Progress summary, next stream preview, patron thanks

Cooldown (post-stream)
  → Holdt Loop + rolling patron credits
  → Viewers linger, smooth exit
```

**Strategic intent:** A fantasy world built in public. A writer's process as the show. Community through creative transparency. Optimized for consistency, authenticity, and repeat engagement — not volume or spectacle.

**Core loop:** Write in public → Engage the community → Invite viewers deeper into the Outside Inn → Repeat weekly.

